ce:section.ce:para:
Regarding rates, the HO concentration produced during ultrasound exposure was linearly proportional to the reaction time (Fig. 6
                         (a)). Thus, the slope of the regression line represented the HO production rate. Following a similar method, we compared the HO production rate from SonoCYL with other conventional reactors including the immersed horn reactor, the cup-horn reactor, and the bath reactor (Table 1
                        ). SonoCYL had at least three orders of magnitude faster HO production rate compared to the immersed horn reactor and five orders of magnitude faster than the cup-horn reactor. There was no observable production of HO for the bath reactor.
